cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper proposes a method to reduce the computational and memory resources required for deep convolutional neural networks. The paper focuses on improving the accuracy of image classification tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The method involves introducing small auxiliary connections to existing convolutional layers, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses stochastic gradient descent, which is a popular optimization algorithm in neural networks and falls under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on ImageNet classification, which is a common benchmark dataset in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV).
